.TH IMG2ANS 1 "2026-03-14" "img2ans" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
img2ans \- convert images to ANSI art
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B img2ans
[\fIoptions\fR] \fIinput\fR [\fIoutput.ans\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B img2ans
converts PNG, JPEG, or BMP images to CP437 ANSI art files suitable for
telnet BBSs, ANSI viewers, and terminals.
.PP
Images are scaled to fit the requested column width, sampled at 8x16 pixel
glyph resolution, and each cell is matched to the best combination of
CP437 block character (space, shades, half-blocks) and 16-color ANSI
foreground/background attribute.
.PP
Output is a raw CP437 byte stream with minimized ANSI SGR escape sequences.
An optional SAUCE metadata record can be appended.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BI \-\-cols " N"
Width of the output in character columns.
Default: 80.
.TP
.BI \-\-rows " N"
Height of the output in character rows.
Default: auto (preserves the image aspect ratio, assuming square pixels
and a 2:1 cell aspect ratio).
.TP
.BI \-\-palette " NAME"
Color palette to use for the 16-color quantization.
.RS
.TP
.B vga
Standard VGA/DOS colors (default).
.TP
.B win
Windows console colors.
.RE
.TP
.B \-\-ice
Enable iCE colors.
Allows all 16 colors as background (without blinking).
By default, only the 8 dark background colors are used.
.TP
.BI \-\-dither " MODE"
Dithering algorithm.
.RS
.TP
.B fs
Floyd-Steinberg error diffusion (default).
.TP
.B atkinson
Atkinson dithering; retains more detail in highlights.
.TP
.B none
No dithering; fastest, produces harder edges.
.RE
.TP
.BI \-\-metric " MODE"
Color distance metric used for palette matching.
.RS
.TP
.B rm
Redmean weighted Euclidean distance (default).
Good perceptual quality with low computational cost.
.TP
.B rgb
Plain sRGB Euclidean distance.
Fast but less perceptually accurate.
.TP
.B ycbcr
YCbCr-space distance with saturation-boosted chroma weight.
Can improve color fidelity for vivid images.
.RE
.TP
.B \-\-sauce
Append a SAUCE metadata record to the output file.
.TP
.BI \-\-title " STR"
Set the SAUCE title field (implies
.BR \-\-sauce ).
Maximum 35 characters.
.TP
.BI \-\-author " STR"
Set the SAUCE author field (implies
.BR \-\-sauce ).
Maximum 20 characters.
.TP
.BI \-\-group " STR"
Set the SAUCE group field (implies
.BR \-\-sauce ).
Maximum 20 characters.
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Print a usage summary and exit.
.SH "OUTPUT FORMAT"
The output file is a raw byte stream containing CP437 characters interleaved
with ANSI X3.64 SGR escape sequences for color and attribute control.
Lines are terminated with CR+LF for maximum ANSI viewer compatibility.
.PP
When
.B \-\-sauce
is given, an EOF marker byte (0x1A) followed by a 128-byte SAUCE record is
appended after the last line.
.SH EXAMPLES
Convert an image to an 80-column ANSI file:
.PP
.RS
img2ans logo.png logo.ans
.RE
.PP
Convert with iCE colors and custom dimensions:
.PP
.RS
img2ans \-\-cols 80 \-\-rows 50 \-\-ice banner.png banner.ans
.RE
.PP
Convert with SAUCE metadata:
.PP
.RS
img2ans \-\-title "My Logo" \-\-author "SysOp" \-\-group "ACiD" logo.png logo.ans
.RE
.PP
Convert with Atkinson dithering and YCbCr color matching:
.PP
.RS
img2ans \-\-dither atkinson \-\-metric ycbcr photo.jpg photo.ans
.RE
.SH BUILDING
Requires a C99 compiler.
.B stb_image.h
must be present in the same directory.
No other external dependencies.
.PP
.RS
make
.br
sudo make install
.RE
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.BR convert (1),
.BR ffmpeg (1)
.SH LICENSE
